I basically explained that

00:00:40.720 --> 00:00:44.680
our modern monetary systems,
the money system of the UK,

00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:48.200
the US or Europe of basically
the whole rich world at the moment

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:52.000
is a debt based money system,
which means that money is debt.

00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:54.720
And what I said
at the beginning of that video was that

00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:58.720
if we added up the total amount of money
in the whole of society,

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:00.320
it would add up to zero.

00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:03.320
And that is because we have a debt
based money system,

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:06.280
which means that for every one person
with £1 of money,

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:10.320
there has to be somebody somewhere
with £1 of debt and it cancels out.

00:01:11.120 --> 00:01:13.240
I think that can be a little bit confusing
for some people.

00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:15.560
When we think about it
from the money perspective,

00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:17.640
but now we can look at it
from the debt perspective.

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:23.040
And I think that makes it a bit clearer
because it should be easy to understand

00:01:23.160 --> 00:01:27.880
that the total amount of debt in society
is equal to zero.

00:01:27.880 --> 00:01:31.760
And the way that you should be able
to understand that is because we know

00:01:32.120 --> 00:01:34.760
that it is impossible to be in debt

00:01:35.160 --> 00:01:38.360
without being in debt to somebody.

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:41.760
So if we add up the total amount of debt,
it will equal the total

00:01:41.760 --> 00:01:44.720
amount of money owed to somebody.

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:47.120
The amount of money
that everybody owes is equal

00:01:47.120 --> 00:01:48.960
to the amount of money
that everybody is owed.

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:49.560
And that is because

00:01:49.560 --> 00:01:53.480
every debt has somebody who is in debt
and somebody who is in credit.

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:57.800
And we're going to use that term ‘credit’
to refer to having money owed to you.

00:01:58.040 --> 00:02:02.960
So if I borrow £100 from Simran,
then I have £100 of debt.

00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:03.560
I'm in debt.

00:02:03.560 --> 00:02:04.960
And Simran has £100 of credit.

00:02:04.960 --> 00:02:06.680
He is in credit because I owe him money.

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:09.320
So this is the

00:02:09.320 --> 00:02:12.480
first thing that debt adds up to zero.

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:16.080
And it's obvious when you think about it
because you know that if you owe money,

00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:18.440
then you owe that money to somebody.

00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:21.720
Is it possible to owe money to nobody?

00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:27.520
But I think as much as it's obvious
when you think about it very often in

00:02:28.040 --> 00:02:32.880
our conversation about debt, it becomes
clear that we don't really think about it.

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:36.320
Because, for example,
we know in the last three years

