00:08:59.120 --> 00:09:01.000
Now, the next thing I want to explain

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:04.080
is a little bit tricky, but I think it's
important to understand the function

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:08.400
that debt plays in our economy,
which is that debt is a form of ownership.

00:09:08.400 --> 00:09:12.520
It and I think the best way to understand
this is to consider

00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:16.880
the way in which corporations
finance themselves.

00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:21.760
So we tend to know about shareholders,
which is if corporations need money,

00:09:22.080 --> 00:09:24.760
they sell shares,
they get money from the shareholders,

00:09:24.760 --> 00:09:28.200
and the shareholders give the money
to the company that it needs.

00:09:28.200 --> 00:09:31.240
But in actuality, corporations

00:09:31.240 --> 00:09:35.000
choose largely
between two ways of raising funds,

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:39.720
which is selling shares to shareholders
and selling bonds, which is essentially

00:09:39.720 --> 00:09:43.320
borrowing money from wealthy people
who want to lend money.

00:09:44.040 --> 00:09:48.600
And in many cases
they take more than 50% of their funding

00:09:49.080 --> 00:09:52.080
from people
who lend the money to them, to creditors.

00:09:52.480 --> 00:09:56.200
So when you are running a corporation,
you have a choice between

00:09:56.200 --> 00:10:00.720
how do you raise funds from stockholders
or from bondholders?

00:10:00.720 --> 00:10:02.280
Who are the people who lend the money?

00:10:02.280 --> 00:10:04.560
And when you think about it
like this, you realise that

00:10:05.520 --> 00:10:09.080
stockholders and bondholders 
are really not that different.

00:10:09.600 --> 00:10:11.920
They are both people
that give money to a corporation

00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:15.920
and then take a share of the profits
of the corporation.

00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:18.520
The way in which the profits are shared
is different.

00:10:18.520 --> 00:10:23.600
So the company first has to pay interest
to the bondholders.

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:27.240
Then if there's any money left,
it pays the rest of the profits

00:10:27.800 --> 00:10:28.800
to the shareholders.

00:10:28.800 --> 00:10:31.040
But in a sense, it's not that different.

00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:34.600
If you are a bond holder or stockholder,
you give money to the company

00:10:34.600 --> 00:10:36.720
and they give you a share of their profits
going forward.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:39.960
So we consider often in our mind

00:10:39.960 --> 00:10:42.760
the stockholders
to be the owners of the company,

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:48.120
but in a very real way, stockholders
and bondholders are not that different.

00:10:49.240 --> 00:10:52.040
And it's the same if you own a house.

00:10:52.680 --> 00:10:56.720
So obviously, if you buy a house,
you think you own the house.

00:10:57.480 --> 00:10:59.960
But if you buy a house
using a huge amount of debt,

00:11:00.560 --> 00:11:06.080
then really your situation is in many ways
similar to when you were still renting.

00:11:06.080 --> 00:11:07.840
Right. You know, of course,
there are differences.

00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:09.840
You can choose what to put on the walls
and things like this.

00:11:09.840 --> 00:11:12.200
But if you're renting a house,

00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:14.120
you live in the house
and you have to pay a chunk of money

00:11:14.120 --> 00:11:16.800
every month to the owner of the house
to live in the house.

00:11:17.360 --> 00:11:20.160
If you're owning with a mortgage,
you live in the house and you have to pay

00:11:20.160 --> 00:11:24.560
a chunk of money to the moneylender
every month to live in the house.

00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:28.360
So I think it's important
to understand that really

00:11:30.080 --> 00:11:31.880
debt is

00:11:31.880 --> 00:11:34.960
a form of owning assets.

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:38.840
It's it's not that dissimilar
to simply owning the asset and renting it.

00:11:39.520 --> 00:11:42.680
And in both cases, you'll see
if you stop making the payments.

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:45.520
So if a corporation stops
making the payments to the debt holders,

00:11:46.120 --> 00:11:49.400
what will happen is legally
the debt holders will be given

00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:52.400
possession of the company
because there is a form of ownership.

00:11:52.760 --> 00:11:56.120
And if you stop paying your mortgage,
what will happen is your mortgage

00:11:56.120 --> 00:11:58.520
lender will take
legal possession of your house

00:11:58.520 --> 00:12:02.000
because debt is a form of ownership
and I think it's

00:12:03.440 --> 00:12:06.760
it's important to understand that

00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:10.640
that basic fact really
that that debt is a form of ownership.

00:12:10.640 --> 00:12:12.960
And if you own an asset
with a large amount of debt,

00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:16.400
essentially
what is happening is a wealthy person

00:12:16.400 --> 00:12:20.520
who has the money to lend you
is buying the asset through you.

00:12:20.640 --> 00:12:24.160
And of course,
debt is not the same as ownership, right?

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:28.640
If you own the property with debt, you
you take the price risk on the property.

00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:30.760
If the price goes up, you make that money.

00:12:30.760 --> 00:12:32.960
If the price goes down,
you lose that money.

00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:35.480
Also, you have the the legal risk.

00:12:35.480 --> 00:12:38.720
So we have a situation in this country
where a lot of people bought property

00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:43.600
and then found that they had to upgrade
the cladding on their property

00:12:43.600 --> 00:12:46.160
and the owner had to take the
loss on that.

00:12:46.880 --> 00:12:47.720
So if you own

00:12:48.680 --> 00:12:50.280
with debt, then you take

00:12:50.280 --> 00:12:53.600
price risk, you take legal risk
and you also have to manage the property.

00:12:54.120 --> 00:12:58.640
But in a very real sense, you
if you have to pay to use that thing,

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:03.080
be that through owning it or through
having debt, you do not own that property.

00:13:03.080 --> 00:13:07.520
So debt is a form of ownership
and it is a way of rich people

00:13:08.040 --> 00:13:11.320
buying assets
and not having to worry about the price

00:13:11.320 --> 00:13:14.000
going down,
not having to worry about management,

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:16.160
not having to worry about about legal
risk.

00:13:16.640 --> 00:13:19.880
Really,
if you think about it from the perspective

00:13:19.880 --> 00:13:23.120
of the wealthy lender, it's
kind of he's kind of running a business.

00:13:23.120 --> 00:13:24.640
He's saying, look,

00:13:25.560 --> 00:13:26.960
I have two ways of getting property.

00:13:26.960 --> 00:13:28.800
Either I buy it and I read it to you,

00:13:28.800 --> 00:13:30.800
but then I take the risk
of the price falling.

00:13:30.960 --> 00:13:35.560
I take the risk of damage, I take legal
